OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772179261
OL,3,CConcerns raised over 'family voting'
OL,4,Cin Gorton and Denton by-election
OL,6,FThe Greens expressed confidence that
OL,7,Ftheir vote had held up well, with Mr
OL,8,FPolanski telling Newsnight: "When I
OL,9,Fbecame leader six months ago, if you'd
OL,10,Ftold me we could seriously come second
OL,11,Fplace or even first place in a by-
OL,12,Felection and challenge this Labour
OL,13,FGovernment in what used to be called a
OL,14,Fsafe Labour seat, I'd say that's
OL,15,Fpretty remarkable."
OL,17,FReform UK chair David Bull said: "It's
OL,18,Fa three way marginal, we're seeing the
OL,19,FGreens and Labour fighting each other
OL,20,F(and) there is a possible we can go
OL,21,Fstraight through the middle."
OL,26,@pD@]OUwD@SO]yD@bOU|D@Apm|D@Epn}D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/15
